node.title: Victoria records 1,362 new COVID-19 cases and seven deaths
node.alt: Queen Victoria Market with Melbourne's cityscape behind it
node.description: There are now 10,887Â active cases of COVID in the state, as the death toll for the current outbreak rises to 494.
node.content:
["Victoria has recorded 1,362\u00a0new local COVID-19 cases and seven\u00a0deaths as the state\u00a0enjoys a rolling back of border restrictions.", "There\u00a0are now 10,887\u00a0active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 494\u00a0people have died during the state's current Delta outbreak.", "There are 308\u00a0people in hospital with COVID-19, of whom 46\u00a0are in intensive care and 26\u00a0are on a ventilator.", "The health department said a further 53\u00a0people were in intensive care but their COVID-19 infections were no longer considered active.", "Victoria yesterday reached 90 per cent double dose vaccination for those aged 12 and over, abolishing the traffic light border scheme and all domestic border permits, regardless of vaccination status.", "", "
What COVID-19 travel insurance doesn't cover you for(Emilia Terzon)
"]
